org.swisscheese.swisscheese.engine.keyboard

Enum Keys

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Keys>
      • org.swisscheese.swisscheese.engine.keyboard.Keys
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Keys>

    public enum Keys
extends java.lang.Enum<Keys>
    ENUMS for the Keyboard. All the usable keys for the game. While the list is limited, ENUMS allows more keys to be added in the future as needed.

    All Keys are initialized as without an action. Key Action Setter will be used to load the setting from a file. User can change the preferences and key-bindings, and the game will open with the new key bindings.

    Since:
    2018-12-1, v0.2
    Version:
    v1.0
    Author:
    Alex Kalinins
